value.0: Kiffex is the smaller sister planet of Kiffu in the Azurbani system of the Inner Rim. It has rich soil, giving Kiffex the potential to become a major agriculture producing planet. It contains prison colonies for Kiffu's sector, overseen by the Kiffu Guardians, serving as a Republic prison world since at least 3,000 BBY

Thyferra is a hot, humid planet located in the Polith system on the Rimma Trade Route. It is on Thyferra where almost all of the Galaxy's bacta is produced. Thyferra is the homeworld of the Vratix people.

Kinyen is an agriworld in the Expansion Region, located on the Corellian Trade Spine. It is the Gran home world, with a recorded history dating back to 10,000 BBY. During its recorded history, the planet has had no local wars.

The planet itself boasts many differing climates, large and rolling grasslands, a dense and beautiful forest, and one of the longest and clearest rivers in the Sumitra Sector. The beauty of this planet, which boasts almost no natural predators, help the Gran develop strong bonds of home and family in their race. With such close bonds formed throughout the Gran community, it is not surprising that they concentrate their cities into very small areas, so they are never out of touch with their many relatives. Oftentimes, families adopt the lovable native Houjix as pets. The two main cities are Kinyen Prime on the north continent and Hekaras on the south.

Byss is a planet in the Deep Core, near the center of the Galaxy, discovered no earlier than 45 BBY. A local day lasts 31 standard hours, and a local year lasts 207 standard days. It is the endpoint of the Byss Run.

Abregado-rae is a major manufacturing and trade-oriented planet in the Abregado system in the Core Worlds, sitting at the beginning of the Rimma Trade Route. It is also the beginning of the Shapani Bypass or the "Bacta Run." It has a reputation as one of the Core Worlds' more rough-and-tumble planets. It is home to the infamous Abregado-rae Spaceport.
Ghorman is a planet in the system of the same name in the Sern Sector of the Colonies region. It is the site of the infamous Ghorman Massacre. Fang Zar has a residence on the planet.

Giju is the Herglic homeworld. It is on the Rimma Trade Route and is one endpoint of the Giju Passage. The Herglic developed hyperdrive 25,000 BBY and colonized many nearby planets in what became Herglic Space, establishing the Herglic Trade Empire. The Trade Empire collapsed 13,720 BBY. In 12,720 BBY, the Herglic established contact with the Human colonists of nearby Tapani Sector. The planet joined the Galactic Republic. Giju has many spaceports and manufacturing centers.

Fondor is world famous for its extensive orbital shipyards, outclassed only by those at Corellia and Kuat. These shipyards are still associated with the Techno Union prior to the Clone Wars, and are sufficiently vast enough to construct Darth Vader's Executor-class Star Dreadnought.

Bestine IV is an aquacultural planet in the Inner Rim Territories, near the Corellian Trade Spine. Nearly its entire surface is covered by a vast ocean, but there are many rugged islands spread across the planet.

Devaron is the home world of the Devaronians. It is located in the Colonies. The planet is made up of low mountains and deep valleys linked by thousands of rivers. It is located near the Corellian Trade Spine. The planet has strict capital punishment and a matriarchal government.

Kiffu was the homeworld of the Kiffar, a Near-Human species known to maintain their independence vigorously.[4]

Kiffu was the larger sister world of Kiffex.[3][4] When the two worlds' elliptical orbits would bring them close together, large electrical storms would be generated in Kiffu's atmosphere. The Kiffar harnessed the lightning to provide electrical energy.[3]
